Behind the scenes: 👀 in 2019, new Airbus aircraft have joined our fleet. 🛫 But how does the phase-in of additional airplanes actually work? Find out on our #AustrianBlog.📝 #Servus #InsideAustrian https://t.co/JXkU8H8Rlg https://t.co/G07Ul9jivQ

Austrian Airlines aims to grow in a CO2 neutral manner. We have committed ourselves to this goal within the context of the “CORSIA” agreement. As of 2021, CO2 emissions generated by international air traffic will be compensated by investments in climate protection projects. @icao https://t.co/KMZ9LkWAYg

Since 2008 our passengers can compensate the CO2 emissions of their flight. To date, around 100,000 tonnes of CO2 were offset. Compensation can't prevent emissions, but it's important for more sustainable flying until alternative fuels can be used on a large scale. #mindfultravel https://t.co/lbB083veKT

data.text: Wing, oh wing right by my side. Reflect my colors, for they shine bright. What's your rhyme for this great pic taken by our fan Tobi? Thank you very much good sir! 🙏 #WingWednesday https://t.co/XwQ09srG9E

In 2014 we launched AIRail together with @unsereOEBB. In this cooperation we wanted to combine plane & train. Today up to 35 daily AIRail connections are available bearing an Austrian Airlines flight number. Over 100,000 guests used this offering by now. Happy to be part of this! https://t.co/PeW2YxDzzx

Our aim is to save 4,000 tons of kerosene a year leading to a reduction of CO2 emissions by 11,000 tons annually. For this we are implementing several projects, for example Single Engine Taxi-In on our Airbus fleet - a procedure already in use at our Dash fleet. #mindfultravel https://t.co/OShH78qZOB

And there she is: Zulu-Fox on her way to #Berlin @B_TXL. The @AirbusPRESS A320 is our youngest fleet member and the only one with so called “sharklets” on the wings. Thanks to https://t.co/gAtil5kMlM for this great night shot on one of her first flights 📸 #spotter #aviation https://t.co/hcD9r6rYom
60 years ago we flew to Athens and Cairo for the first time. Today both capital cities are still an integral part of our flight schedule! 🇬🇷🇪🇬 #MondayMotivation https://t.co/Pv9sIXbFKG

Ups, we did it again! Just been awarded with the title “Best Cabin Crew in Europe” by @airlinequality 🇦🇹🤗🥇#1 #skytrax #SimplyTheBest #cabincrew #flightattendant #aviation #quality 
https://t.co/TtzDFsuDEi https://t.co/ljtIWKaPzV
@eurowings "Mr. O'Leary is wrong if he thinks, that he can overtake us here in Vienna", says CEO Alexis von Hoensbroech.
"We are holding our position here, also with the help of @eurowings and the four aircraft we could lease from them", says CEO Alexis von Hoensbroech.
"We aim to reduce costs via efficiency and productivity improvements. The long-term objective is to modernize our fleet and then once again return to a strong growth path", says CFO Wolfgang Jani.
"We will maintain our premium strategy. We will bundle our fleet strength stationing all our aircraft available here in Vienna", says CCO Andreas Otto.
"Let me get this straight: We will not retreat a single millimeter on the Viennese market", says CCO Andreas Otto.
"Not every competition is fair. Employees' rights are being attacked. We, in contrast, have the best collective agreement here in Vienna", says CEO Alexis von Hoensbroech.
"The tough competition in Vienna is costing everyone dearly. However, we currently still make a profit in contrast to our competitors", says CEO Alexis von Hoensbroech.
"Our hub in Vienna is currently being flooded by low-cost airlines. This development will continue", says CEO Alexis von Hoensbroech.
We will soon tweet live updates from our press conference concerning our Q1-Q3 numbers and strategy in Vienna. Stay tuned! https://t.co/ksl2Xw9iLJ

“We succeeded in attracting additional customers in despite of the competition from low-cost airlines”, states Austrian Airlines CFO Wolfgang Jani. “However, the glut of budget airlines in Vienna & higher jet fuel costs intensify pressure on ticket prices & thus on our earnings.” https://t.co/wHBR6gbwTi

The regularity of operation in the first three quarters of 2019 rose to a gratifying level of 99.0 percent (Q1-3 2018: 97.8 percent). Punctuality on departure and punctuality on arrival could both be slightly improved to 75.0 percent and 79.2 percent respectively. https://t.co/a8cd2zyTmw

Austrian Airlines reported an adjusted EBIT of EUR 17 million for the first three quarters of 2019. Revenue fell by two percent to EUR 1,696 million in spite of passenger growth. Total operating expenditures rose by four percent to EUR 1,679 million in the same period. https://t.co/uO8v0DGA8U

Last week a Vienna Ball took place for the first time in Cape Town - including Lipizzaner and Wiener Sängerknaben. Thanks to all organizers and supporters. Over 26,000 euros could be handed over to the iThemba school project of #helpalliance in Cape Town. https://t.co/rFjzxyPQn6
